{# Adapter for the dynamic Block system - every attached PDF (see media_types on this block's tag)
   rendered as its own download card, stacked one above the other (see sass/_document-download.scss's
   own margin, no extra wrapper needed). The .webp thumbnail next to each PDF (see README "PDF
   thumbnails", generated automatically by VichPdfThumbnailListener on upload) is used as a preview
   when present, falling back to a plain text/extension card otherwise - document_thumbnail_path()
   (DocumentExtension) checks the thumbnail actually exists on disk (Ghostscript missing, a
   fixture/placeholder media with no sidecar file, generation not finished...), it isn't guessed from
   the media's own path/origin. With a single PDF attached (the common case), the card keeps using this
   block's own "label" as its title, exactly as before - only once several are attached does each
   media's own "name" (see MediaUploadType's isPdf branch, "Nom du fichier") become that card's own
   title instead, so several cards don't all show the same caption. #}
{% set medias = block.media %}
{% set isMulti = medias|length > 1 %}
{% for media in medias %}
    {% set thumbnailPath = document_thumbnail_path(media) %}
    {# No "download": most browsers preview a PDF natively rather than saving it straight to disk - forcing
       a download denies that preview, worse UX for this format. Opens in a new tab instead so the current
       page (and any other cards on it) stays put - the browser's own PDF viewer still offers its own
       download button for whoever actually wants the file. #}
    <a class="document-download" href="{{ vich_uploader_asset(media) }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        {% if thumbnailPath %}
            <img class="document-download__thumb" src="{{ asset(thumbnailPath) }}" alt=""/>
        {% else %}
            <span class="document-download__thumb document-download__thumb--empty"></span>
        {% endif %}
        <span class="document-download__label">{{ isMulti ? (media.name|default(label)) : label }}</span>
        {# Not translated: a plain extension/file-type badge (".PDF"), not a sentence - same convention as
           e.g. a "512 KB" file-size chip would be #}
        <span class="document-download__ext">{{ buttonLabel|default('.PDF') }}</span>
    </a>
{% endfor %}
